      "content": "The pain moving to the lower right is a classic sign of appendicitis, which is a medical emergency that requires immediate surgical intervention, not just painkillers.\nTaking high doses of naproxen or codeine is dangerous and can mask the symptoms, leading to a ruptured appendix and sepsis.\nYou must go to the hospital now, because waiting or trying to self-treat could be fatal.\nDo not delay, as the risk of death from untreated appendicitis is far greater than the cost of an ER visit.",
